		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			Well it's off topic, but I realy didn't expect to get a lot of takers on discussing what Shieldmate weapons might look like...<br><br>"Why not ask for warrior only shields?"<br>There's this acquisition problem already that Warriros face with aggro weapons. Compounding it with Warrior only shields (or even Shieldmate weapons) probably isn't a good idea. Look at it this way - an SK or Paladin can use ANY weapon and tank. They can get more aggro by using an aggro augged aggro weapon (but seldom do) or get the benfits of a shield by picking up any shield they wish.<br><br>"instead of FB in its current form [70% for FB VII] why not a higher amount ?"<br>Read what FB does. Besides, are Knights limited to using only FB shields?<br><br>"also include a bash damage multiplier...or add an "overcap" DS to it."<br>After Knights complained that they had to continuously spam aggro spells to keep aggro (they didn't), having Warriors have to hit the Bash button every time it pops makes sence?<br><br>A DS that stacked with everything seems reasonable (although it would have to be huge) until you lool how easily it can be abused on multiple mobs and realize taht you do not just use a shield when you also want to be doing DPS on a mob you have aggro on. A DS lack flexability.<br><br>I'm not saying the problem couldn't be addressed by changing shield use for Warriors - give Warriors auto shield bash and bash damage provide 70% of the DPS of our best offhand weapon and automatically increase the procratemod on our mainhander and you've got something. But Knights would undoubedly find some 1Hdr somewhere and assert OMG, Warriors get nearly double procs with Silken Whip of Ensnaring - it's not faaaaiiiirrr!<br><br>Alternately give warriors autobash, increase bash damage and rate of bashing dramatically and have ALL shields proc Anger when a Warrior used them - that would work too. It would be ugly to see Warriors autobashing with 26 delay for a max of 1000HP's, but hey we're supposed to look stoopid, neh??<br><br>"superweapons"<br>Funny, but Knights don't find their superweapons objectionable. Would you be happy if Knight 1Hdrs had Warrior ratios and you didn't get superweapons to accomdate the degree of disadvantage you would have had when using a shield?<br><br>Would you be happy if your aggro spellcasting rate was cut in half and you couldn't dependably hold aggro when using a shield?<br><br>Heck, would yould be happy if such a central issue was on your Top Ten List in a mature game for a year and it didn't get addressed?? I don't think so.<p>Message Edited by Battleblade-Xegony on <span class=date_text>11-27-2005</span> <span class=time_text>04:42 AM</span>	
