<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
Reply <a href="/eq/board/message?board.id=warriorbalance&message.id=12635#M12635">15</a> of 1531
</span>

			<br><img src="/i/p.gif" width=1 height=6><br>
			<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
			
					Viewed 2215 times<br>
					
			</span>
			
		</td>
		
		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			Here is the problem with all your examples, they are all planned tanking situations.  I am talking about trash plowing.  I had no problems with aggro on planned events as I had time to get a few spells off before melee set in, plus those werent daily deals, so I didnt have to spam spells daily on planned stuff, just on trash clears.  Also, when grouped with guildies, the same problems applied, melee hopped on trash mobs soon as they got in camp, and I lose aggro if I try to say anything.  I hated this when I was in a chain pulling guild group.<br><br>Now whats funny is the major change to aggro was for high end paladins with the oow ancient stun.  This affects nobody but high end paladins, as it doesnt change your job, doesnt change sk's jobs, it just made us able to do our job in a friendlier light.  It made it so I could chat in groups, on raids, and yadi yadi yada while I am playing eq.  It basically made my playing experience more enjoyable as pressing non stop 1/3/5 or clicking 3 stuns non stop got old ages ago, and got really old when mobs started stunning me more than they used to in past expansions.  By me being stunned by newer mobs more often, it made it so half the time on raids, I would be stunned before my first or 2nd stun landed, and I would lose aggro.  You may not realize what being stunned can do to knight aggro, but it isnt pretty, and its very annoying.<br><br>Lets see, as for my killing record.  All of omens down, all of don down, all of tacvi down.  All but spider queen pre demi plane down.  So yes, I have killed a few things.  I have never been a part of the gimme crowd, but asking to be able to enjoy grouping again if you are in a high end guild is not being part of the gimme crowd.  Its a fix to a paladin problem, pure and simple.  SoE made the point that they want people to enjoy the game when they gave bards melody.  So it was not unfair when they let paladins have the choice of not having to act like a bard to hold aggro, it was a chance to let paladins enjoy grouping with their guildies, and their epic 1.5/darkglint blade wielding ranger friends (personal gripe).<br><br>Btw, I am so happy you can get a symbol of the planesmaster on your pally.  They all went to warriors in my guild when we did time, and the only person to throw off day twink a thons in time since then was a warrior officer in my guild, and everytime we went there, the symbol went to new warriors in guild who didnt have it yet.  I am so glad you pharm time enough and have enough symbols drop to get your paladin one.  Oh, and in case you dont remember, you have access to 2 aggro changed spells, and one of them is mana intensive and not an aggro tool.  The other 2 stuns are raider only, unless you buy an ancient from GoD(which sadly connected paladins can), or you are a anguish raider and get one of many rotting ancient runes if you have been pharming there for more than 2 months.  In either case you either need connections, or to be a high end raider, meaning it will still mostly only be people who group with high end raiders who will be getting those stuns.<br><br>As for aggro procs on weapons...  I dont have epic 2, I use a boff auged with enraging blow.  It doesnt work, unless you already have alot of aggro from other sources, and on trash you dont have time to let those procs work in either groups or raids.  I neither have a increased proc rate weapon, a echo of anger item (which will hopefully change someday), or a symbol of the planesmaster or other clicky proc stun item.  And I dont think paladins should be required to have aggro proc's on their weapons.  We have never been required to have them before, and shouldnt be "required" to have them in the future.  That is why all knight weapons have come with heal procs or life tap procs for the most part.  Our aggro is spell based, not melee based, thats your field.  <br><br>If you want more aggro, be my guest, ask away.  If you can come up with a good enough reason besides the paladins got more aggro, I may even agree with you.  But I find it funny that your biggest aggro concerns were taunt until our best stuns got upgraded, the stuns a majority of eq dont have half of.  I also find it funny that you think paladin aggro is done with no aggro.  Group with your guildies with your paladin, and just use piety, akilae, and cease, see how much fun it is.  Dont let your guildies treat your paladin like a gimp, tell them to treat him like a guilded tank.  Do the same after you get an ancient or 2, and just use 2 stuns then and see how hte aggro goes.  See if you can go 6 mobs in rss or similiar hp'ed mobs and see if you dont lose aggro once or twice using 2 stuns.  I can handle using 2 stuns and losing aggro occasionally, but having to use 3 stuns because I would lose aggro everytime if I used two got old very long ago, roughly around when guild monks started getting staff's from inktuta back in GoD.	
		</td></tr>
