<BLOCKQUOTE>
<HR>
BruennorB wrote:<BR>So let me get this straight, you have a problem with an item, and with lower lv aggro, yet you and others want to give the high end paladins a hard time?<BR><BR>Also, I dont care about perks on weapons, I just dont think we should be required to have to get our aggro from weapons, as we have never had to before thanks to the uber flash of light, and then stuns when they became high aggro. Also, aggro got upgraded on mainly raider spells, in case you missed that. High end warrior aggro is already awesome, to the point that I may keep a mob on me 5 to 8 seconds on a trash plow in anguish, but the warrior who got on the mob when I did will have it glued to him most of hte time after that 5 to 8 seconds. It makes me grind my teeth trying to out aggro a high end warrior. It has gotten to the point that if a warrior appears on hott when we are plowing trash on raids, I just dont bother to try for aggro anymore. It certainly lets me be a lazy paladin, even when I dont want to be.<BR><BR>To say this one last time, paladins being required to spam stuns was a broken model in the high end as proven by the creation of melody and autofire. Now paladins are fixed for the time being, unless melee dps skyrockets again in the high end, but soe is heading that off through itemization. I dont know if its a good idea or not, but you obviously think not, so maybe you should quit giving paladins grief and take your arguement to the people who are in charge.<BR>
<HR>
</BLOCKQUOTE><BR>
<DIV></DIV>
<P>Because this myth keeps coming up again and again, I've taken the liberty of taking some FRAPS video showing the unbelievable aggro differential, particularly early on in fights.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Soon as&nbsp;I find a place to host it I'll be more than happy to show you once and for all how absurd this idea of '5-8 seconds and it's glued' really is, and I've actually gone out and done the work to get the most aggro from gear possible.</P>
<P>Furthermore, this notion that the bulk of the upgrades were raider specific is also wrong.&nbsp;&nbsp; Completely wrong.&nbsp; 3 spells were upgraded, two of which are now researchable, one of which is your raid level spell.&nbsp; 1/3 does not make a Majority, even using Paladin math.&nbsp; Furthermore, the mobs that paladins at level 68 and 69 aren't at the hp cap, so it was even more of an upgrade for them than for raiding paladins.&nbsp;&nbsp; </P>
<P>I would be *<STRONG>grateful</STRONG>* if I "had to spam" something to maintain Paladinlike aggro, not complaining.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Furthermore, addng the 20% hate mod was icing on the cake.&nbsp;&nbsp; It's completely over the top at that level.&nbsp;&nbsp; </P>
<P>When was the last time warriors had to rely on a 4 expansion old weapon to be only "a large margin' behind Paladins?&nbsp; Oh yeah, Planes of Power...</P>
<P>The belt and a weapon that procced an aggro proc would've been plenty to fix your issue without the spell upgrades... now it's just over the top.&nbsp;&nbsp; </P>
