		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			First off frodlin, what you apparently dont see or dont want to see is stuns on high lv trash like anguish is a very real thing.  We stun a mob, it charges us, half the time it stuns us from melee so we cant get off a 2nd stun immediately.  At this time we lose aggro, and once lost, its a pain to get back.  My paladins 5th birthday is coming on dec 31, so I feel I can say what I just said and it be truthful from my own experiences.  I am not exagerrating, that is how it works, its one reason I try to go for stun resist gear on my pally because I am tired of constantly being stunned when trying to tank and group heal, tank and stun, tank and do anything remotely different than standing there with melee on.  I am not doing too good, only around 18 percent, but it does help occasionaly.<br><br>Second off Frodlin, 4 spells were upgraded, both the GoD and Omens ancients, plus our 2 omens stuns, the 1 sec cast normal 4 second stun stun, and the 10 second, what seems like ages longer casting, push back with damage stun.  For anybody who doesnt raid or has connections to somebody who clears qvic or inktuta, the GoD and omens ancients are a no go, and that is a majority of paladins in eq.  Btw, the paladin math comment wasnt appreciated.<br><br>And no Frodlin, after 2 years you would not like spamming non stop to hold solid aggro.  You assume you would, but until you actually do it for a long time, you will never know the true answer to what you presume.  You may like it at first, but once you start learning that you are forced to spam with your high end guildies, or even mid lv geared friends..(hence the ranger mention in my last post)..but you will learn that after you get in a good group and start chain pulling, and you cant say half a sentence without fear of losing aggro, because it happened so much earlier in the day, then you will understand how it was for us.<br><br>Now yet again, it sounds like your problems are with SoE about itemization, so why are you holding a grudge against high end paladins?  If you think lower end paladins have too much aggro, get soe to put cease and desist on akilae's and piety's timers, though I doubt they will since those spells are used only for aggro since they dont affect anything over lv 55.  You are better off getting the aggro on those 2 spells and the lv 30 stun spell lowered.  You ever think of lobbying for something like that in the name of fair play instead of trying to sound all broken up about high end paladin changes that dont affect you one bit?<br><br>.................................................................<br><br>Now Battleblade.  I disagree that stuns should be changed in any other ways unless all across hte board stun mitigation is made available.  Atm stuns are only pure aggro tools to high end paladins in 95 percent of raid situations, with the other 5 percent being stuff like stunnable wolves in some DoDH raid instances, and what not.  You are the melee aggro class Battleblade, not me, so why are you trying so hard to make me just like you?  I dont want to be like you or I would of made a warrior, I want to be a paladin, a fella who used stuns for almost half a decade to hold aggro.  Due to stuns limited ability on the stuff I fight, I see no problems here, and it seems to me that just like Frodlin, your biggest gripe is with the lower end game, as high end paladins dont pose a thread to "YOU", just a reason for you to argue.  <br><br>As for expecting a free ride, we have always had a mana cost on our aggro, so its not free.  It is basically free, I will agree, but if you arent a high end paladin, it is far from free as their only ability to chain stun a mob is using piety and serenity, the latter of which is very costly mana wise and cant be kept up for more than a few min of casting, or less, before the paladin is oom.  They can use cease or desist, but those have no other function at that lv of the game other than aggro.  So it seems yet again you are in a grumpy mood about lower end pally aggro, because high end paladins dont concern you at all as our aggro doesnt get your jobs, at least it doesnt in my guild.<br><br>Just like Frodlin you are upset over a piece of gear, itemization.  You are taking your hostility out on the wrong people if you are expecting that to get changed.  Try going where your words might actually be listened to instead of taking pot shots at high end paladins who just play the game.  Because when its all said and done, paladins as a majority backed each other on getting the stun changes, the rational ones are happy.  If you feel like arguing with the irrational ones, go ahead, but quit trying to drag the whole of the paladin class into your arguements with your blanket statements.  <br><br>Btw, the golden haired child comment does indeed show how jaded you are.  Just because we have good aggro without weapons, we are the golden headed step child?  Then how in the world do warriors and sk's get groups if we are that special?  Why is it that other than friends, I only get pick up group invites once every few days with lfg up, and usually only from people I am acquainted with or people who know my guild?  You assume too much, and dont try understanding game play.<p>Message Edited by BruennorB on <span class=date_text>11-27-2005</span> <span class=time_text>06:38 PM</span>	
