			Bruennor,<br><br>"We stun a mob, it charges us, half the time it stuns us from melee so we cant get off a 2nd stun immediately."<br>IF (a big IF concidering the slow refresh on Bazu Bellow) I Bazu a mob, half the time it stuns me from melee. My weapons are not proccing on thier own sir. Despite the fact that you have done NOTHING at all to improve your aggro capability, it sounds to me like you are expecting SPECIAL treatment.<br><br>"At this time we lose aggro, and once lost, its a pain to get back."<br>It's MUCH more of a poain if you've used Bazu and lost aggro sir. Warriors do not have fast repeat at-will aggro capability, taunt doesn't work properly, and your certainly wouldn't want to hang around waiting for procs alone to give you aggro. It sounds to me like you are expecting better than Warrior aggro despite the fact that you have done NOTHING at all to improve your aggro beyond base level.<br><br>"It is basically free..."<br>You should have stopped there Bruennor. It's not basically free, it's so close to an absolutely FREE RIDE it might as well be called what it realy is. Just how much specialized equipment did you have to camp to get those stuns. How many weapons, augs, range items, BP's, gauntlets, did you have to bid DKP on over the years sir? I KNOW what stuns cost to cast. I do not see my mana bar move one iota. In stunnable content they are the biggest mana bargain in the game. A stun is a whole lot cheaper than healing the damage you would have otherwise taken.<br><br>"So it seems yet again you are in a grumpy mood about lower end pally aggro..."<br>Then I suggest you read my posts again. I do not like the FREE RIDE deamands made by mid-tier Pallies that have been complaining since PoP that they should have Defensif. GoD is Tooo Haaard, I shouldn't be made to gear up!! Gimmie gimmie. I'm happy that some of these guilds have progressed in recent expansions, but ANYBODY that complained about GoD post adjustment is not a high-level player in my eyes.<br><br>They horded DKP while Warriors were forced to loot 2 aggro weapons for YEARS, EoA items, a right click item with a weapon aggro buff. And then having not done anything to improve their aggro (an being in a position to do something) for YEARS, they say gimmie better aggro. And when the blessed hand of SoE passes over the head of the Golden Haired Child, how much extra aggro can you generate in 24 seconds? Is it 600 more hate or 800?????<br><br>It's so much aggro that some high-level Paladins are complaining that a 20% EoA aggro multiplier on a belt should be replaced - they don't want it!!!!!!<br><br>No sir, low level Warriors need a weapon or two and low level Paladins do outcalss them. But I'm not annoyed at low level Paladins - almost to a man they weild aggro augged BoDs. The didn't ask for a FREE RIDE. No sir, they worked for what they got and would be foolish not to take advantage of what *cough* high level Paladins "got" them.<br><br>What would you call a Anguish guild Warrior that never obtained and aggro weapon, didn't use aggro augs, never looted Symbol of the Planesmaster or Aten's gloves and had the GALL to complain about aggro? Concider that thought the deed Tank.<p>Message Edited by Battleblade-Xegony on <span class=date_text>11-27-2005</span> <span class=time_text>05:46 PM</span>	
