		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<DIV>Frodlin, you said what&nbsp;I was saying. The same % difference we have between us with twohanded weapons will be the same with sword and board. Because it's the same % difference the ratios still won't be as high as knight weapons precisely due to triple attack and higher damage.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;You do higher damage Frodlin, I was useing a windblade with a warrior useing a windblad and they were landing hits easily 30 points of damage higher than&nbsp;I was and I was 3 levels higher than the warrior. This was during PoP, considerably after Velious.&nbsp; Wether damage charts are higher or higher skill causes more damage&nbsp;I don't know, but the most I could hit with a windblade at the time was 341, they were hitting for 384.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>However if melee dps difference is 25% you couldn't get equally ratioed weapons because of triple attack. If I hit for an average of 250 with a one handed weapon, and&nbsp;I land a double attack for 250's totaling 500. A warrior would also average at least 250's and if they land a triple, they would&nbsp;do 750, wich is 50% higher dps with weapons of the same ratio, let alone weapons of a higher ratio. Throw in higher damage output&nbsp; and the dps difference gets closer to 60%.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>In any event, warriors, because of the extra attack ability, will have higher dps vs knights even with weapons at lower ratios. If it's 25% then it's 25%, I think it's closer to 15% but that's just me. Either way, warrior one handed weapons wouldn't have the same ratio as knight weapons. </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>That doesn't mean I don't think warriors shouldn't get decent agro induceing one handed dps weapons. I'm simply saying that they probably wouldn't be the same ratio as knight one handed weapons, because of the reasons I stated. </DIV>	
		</td></tr>
